The paper presents a technique for boosting the performance of existing stochastic optimization methods in the context of deep learning tasks. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also mentions the application of the method on neural networks, which suggests the possibility of it being relevant to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of the method on image classification tasks, which could indicate relevance to cs.CV (Computer Vision). The method is also applicable to any existing optimization method, which suggests relevance to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper mentions the use of the method for control systems, which could indicate relevance to cs.SY (Systems and Control).
